y period `2025-06-06T10:03:14Z to 2025-06-06T10:17:14Z` has been successfully completed. Significant traces and status combinations have been retrieved for further analysis. Below are the details of the findings:\n\n### Significant Abnormal Traces\n1. Severe latency and connection errors between `frontend` and `RecommendationService` operations. Normal latency was very high (e.g., ~118341ms), but during anomalies, it drastically dropped to ~186ms, with frequent connection refused errors (`28 occurrences` per frontend node).\n2. Latency spikes in calls to `ProductCatalogService` when accessed by `frontend`. An increase from ~10040ms to ~11383-13546ms is observed, with multiple occurrences.\n3. Critical performance degradation in `CheckoutService/PlaceOrder` where latency spiked from ~145475ms to ~243984-272917ms in two significant cases.\n4. Specific service components like `emailservice`, `cartservice`, and `shippingservice` also showed significant latency spikes during this time window, e.g., `CartService` went from ~2314ms to ~20689ms.\n\n### Status Code Errors\n- `Connection refused` error between `frontend` and `RecommendationService` is observed as a dominant issue (~4652 occurrences across nodes).\n- HTTP 500 errors occurred with the `frontend` service (`4081 occurrences` total).\n- Other errors with notable spikes but lower occurrences include transport closing and HTTP 14 status codes.\n\n### Next Steps\nProceeding to analyze the root cause by identifying the most downstream impacted services and their propagation effect across the upstream dependencies."}
